    • Class com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.WebCmsObjectSuperClass extends com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.SettableIdAuditableEntity<T extends WebCmsObjectSuperClass<T>> implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • objectId

          String objectId
          Globally unique id for this object. Alternative for the generated id property as the key should be set manually. Consumer code should use SettableIdBasedEntity.isNew() to determine if the object is represented by a persisted entity or if it is new.

          Can be used for synchronization of assets between environments. Like the regular id the key should preferably never be modified after creation of an entity, as it determines the global identity of the asset.

    • Class com.foreach.across.modules.webcms.domain.page.WebCmsPage extends WebCmsAsset<WebCmsPage> implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • title

          String title
          Title of the page.

        • parent

          WebCmsPage parent
          Parent page. Will determine the administrative hierarchy of pages, but properties from the parent might also be inherited or used for generation of values (depending on settings).

        • pathSegment

          String pathSegment
          Path segment. Used as an identification in the hierarchical context. Every page should have a unique path segment relative to its parents' path, resulting in a globally unique path containing all its ancestors.

        • pathSegmentGenerated

          boolean pathSegmentGenerated
          Should the path segment be generated based on the title.

        • canonicalPath

          String canonicalPath
          Fully qualified canonical path of this page, usually corresponds with the path relative within the application. The canonical path is unique for every page and will always start with a /.

        • canonicalPathGenerated

          boolean canonicalPathGenerated
          Should the canonical path be generated based on the path segment and ancestor pages.

        • template

          String template
          Template to use when rendering the page.
